---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NextSteps from '../components/NextSteps.astro';
---

<BaseLayout description="A field guide to the Transductive Universe.">
  <section class="home-hero">
    <p class="home-wordmark">Ontogony</p>
    <h1 class="home-title">A Field Guide to the Transductive Universe</h1>
    <p class="home-subtitle">
      A theory of becoming — about what it costs for anything to be the kind
      of thing it is, and how new kinds of things come into being at all.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      This site is a working field guide to <a href="/theory">Ontogony</a>:
      short, self-contained entries that map the framework's vocabulary,
      arguments, and through-lines. It is meant to be read piecewise. There is
      no front-to-back order; every page tries to answer the question, “where
      do I go next?”
    </p>
    <p>
      If you have five minutes, start with the <a href="/theory">overview</a>.
      If you want one specific idea, start with the
      <a href="/concepts/transduction">Transduction</a> page — it is the
      operator the rest of the framework is built on.
    </p>
  </div>

  <NextSteps
    heading="Where to begin"
    concepts={['transduction']}
  />
</BaseLayout>
